# --- Gradle task completion via fzf on TAB -----------------------------------
# Dependencies
# - zsh
#   - This script must be sourced by zsh and uses ZLE widgets and ${(z)} word splitting.
#
# - fzf (must support `--listen`)
#   - Unix domain socket mode requires fzf >= 0.66.0 (pass a path ending in `.sock`).
#   - Older versions require TCP mode (`--listen 127.0.0.1:<port>`).
#   - The refresh feature depends on pushing actions to the running instance (e.g. `reload(...)`, `change-header(...)`).
#
# - curl >= 7.40.0
#   - Requires `--unix-socket` so the background refresh can POST actions to the fzf Unix socket.
#
# Specification
#
# Overview
# - Provides an fzf-based completion UI on TAB for Gradle wrapper invocations.
# - Activates only when the current directory is the Gradle root (./gradlew exists and is executable).
#
# Logging
# - Writes log events to `.gradle-completion/log.txt`, relative to the project root directory.
# - Creates `.gradle-completion/` and `log.txt` if they do not exist.
# - Appends one line per event.
# - Uses the format: `<timestamp> <event> [<metadata>]`.
# - Uses a local timestamp formatted like `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+ZZZZ`.
# - Omits the `[<metadata>]` block when there is no metadata.
# - Encodes metadata as a single string (commonly key=value pairs).
#
# Activation
# - Activates when the left buffer (text before the cursor) begins with `gradlew` or `./gradlew`.
# - Activates only when `./gradlew` is present in the current directory and is executable.
# - Uses TAB as the activation key.
# - Falls back to the shell’s default completion (`expand-or-complete`) when not activated.
#
# Candidate source and caching
# - Reads candidates from `.gradle-completion/cached-entries.txt`.
# - Treats each line in the file as one completion candidate.
# - Logs `initial_content_loaded` when candidates are loaded.
# - Sets `source=cache` in the `initial_content_loaded` metadata when the cache file already exists.
# - Runs `initialize.sh <rootDir>` when the cache file does not exist.
# - Logs `initialize` before running `initialize.sh`.
# - Writes the stdout of `initialize.sh` to `.gradle-completion/cached-entries.txt`.
# - Loads candidates from the newly written cache file after initialization.
# - Logs `initial_content_loaded` with `source=initialize` after loading from the newly created cache.
# - Logs `initialize_failed` with `exit=<code>` when `initialize.sh` exits non-zero.
# - Leaves the prompt unchanged when initialization fails.
#
# Refresh
# - Supports refreshing the cache while the fzf UI is open.
# - The user triggers a refresh by pressing Ctrl+R.
# - Runs `refresh.sh <rootDir>` in the background (non-blocking).
# - While refresh is running:
#   - The existing candidate list remains usable.
#   - The header shows a refresh-in-progress indicator.
# - When refresh completes:
#   - If successful, atomically replaces `.gradle-completion/cached-entries.txt` with the refreshed output.
#   - If failed, leaves the existing cache file unchanged.
#   - Clears the refresh-in-progress indicator in the UI header.
#   - Updates the fzf candidate list immediately (without requiring additional user interaction) by sending actions to the running fzf instance via `--listen` (Unix socket).
# - Ignores additional Ctrl+R presses while a refresh is already running.
#
# Expectations on refresh.sh
# - Same as initialize.sh, but may take longer.
# - Accepts exactly one argument: the Gradle project root directory.
# - Prints one completion candidate per line to stdout.
# - Prints any errors to stderr.
# - Exits with a non-zero status on failure.
#
# Refresh logging
# - Logs `refresh_requested` when the user presses Ctrl+R.
# - Logs `refresh_started` when the background refresh begins.
# - Logs `refresh_skipped` with `reason=already_running` when Ctrl+R is pressed during an in-flight refresh.
# - Logs `refresh_finished` with `exit=0` when refresh succeeds.
# - Logs `refresh_failed` with `exit=<code>` when refresh exits non-zero.
#
# Expectations on initialize.sh
# - Accepts exactly one argument: the Gradle project root directory.
# - Assumes the directory is a valid Gradle wrapper project.
# - Prints one completion candidate per line to stdout.
# - Prints any errors to stderr.
# - Exits with a non-zero status on failure.
#
# User interaction behavior
# - Opens an fzf selection UI populated with the candidate list.
# - Treats Ctrl+C and Esc in the fzf UI as cancellation.
# - Restores the original prompt on cancellation.
# - Logs `user_cancelled` when the user cancels the UI.
# - Sets `via=esc` when the user cancels with Escape, and `via=ctrl-c` when the user cancels with Ctrl+C.
# - If the cursor is immediately after a non-whitespace character AND there is at least one argument already present (i.e. the buffer contains more than just the `gradlew`/`./gradlew` command), the last argument token is treated as an initial filter for the fzf list.
# - In that case, fzf starts with the filter pre-filled, and accepting a completion REPLACES the last argument token (does not append).
# - Example: when the prompt is `./gradlew he` and the user accepts `help`, the result becomes `./gradlew help`.
# - Otherwise (cursor after whitespace, or no arguments yet), accepting a completion APPENDS it to the prompt.
# - When appending, inserts a single separating space before the appended completion when the prompt does not already end in whitespace.
# - Shows a header line in the UI containing the current project directory and the cancellation hint.
# - Header format (idle): `<projectDir>  |  Cancel: Esc/Ctrl+c  |  Refresh: Ctrl+r`.
# - Header format (refreshing): `<projectDir>  |  Cancel: Esc/Ctrl+c  |  Refresh: Ctrl+r  |  Refreshing...`.

# --- Implementation ----------------------------------------------------------

# Guard: this script is intended to be sourced from zsh.
if [[ -z ${ZSH_VERSION:-} ]]; then
  return 0 2>/dev/null || exit 0
fi

# Resolve the directory of this sourced script (works when sourced).
# ${(%):-%x} expands to the current sourced file in zsh.
__gradle_fzf_completion__script_path=${${(%):-%x}:A}
__gradle_fzf_completion__script_dir=${__gradle_fzf_completion__script_path:h}

# Utilities
__gradle_fzf_completion__now() {
  # ISO-8601-ish local timestamp
  date "+%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S%z"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__ensure_log_file() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local log_dir="$root_dir/.gradle-completion"
  local log_file="$log_dir/log.txt"
  mkdir -p "$log_dir" 2>/dev/null
  : >| "$log_file" 2>/dev/null || true
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__log() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local event="$2"
  local metadata="$3"

  __gradle_fzf_completion__ensure_log_file "$root_dir"
  local log_file="$root_dir/.gradle-completion/log.txt"

  if [[ -n "$metadata" ]]; then
    print -r -- "$(__gradle_fzf_completion__now) $event [$metadata]" >>| "$log_file" 2>/dev/null || true
  else
    print -r -- "$(__gradle_fzf_completion__now) $event" >>| "$log_file" 2>/dev/null || true
  fi
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__is_gradle_root() {
  # Must be in a directory that contains an executable Gradle wrapper script
  [[ -x "./gradlew" && -f "./gradlew" ]]
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__should_activate() {
  # Trigger only when the left buffer begins with `gradlew` or `./gradlew`
  local lb="$LBUFFER"
  [[ "$lb" == gradlew* || "$lb" == "./gradlew"* ]]
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__fzf_supports_unix_socket_listen() {
  # Unix socket support for --listen was added in fzf 0.66.0.
  local v
  v="$(fzf --version 2>/dev/null | awk '{print $1}')"
  [[ -n "$v" ]] || return 1

  local major="${v%%.*}"
  local rest="${v#*.}"
  local minor="${rest%%.*}"
  local patch="${rest#*.}"
  patch="${patch%%[^0-9]*}"

  [[ "$major" == <-> && "$minor" == <-> && "$patch" == <-> ]] || return 1

  # >= 0.66.0
  if (( major > 0 )); then
    return 0
  fi
  if (( minor > 66 )); then
    return 0
  fi
  if (( minor < 66 )); then
    return 1
  fi
  (( patch >= 0 ))
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__pick_listen_port() {
  # Best-effort random high port on localhost.
  print -r -- $(( 49152 + (RANDOM % 16383) ))
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__cached_entries_file() {
  print -r -- "$1/.gradle-completion/cached-entries.txt"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_pid_file() {
  print -r -- "$1/.gradle-completion/refresh.pid"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_tmp_file() {
  print -r -- "$1/.gradle-completion/cached-entries.txt.refresh.tmp"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_script() {
  # Prefer a refresh.sh next to this completion script, otherwise rely on PATH.
  local script="$__gradle_fzf_completion__script_dir/refresh.sh"
  if [[ -x "$script" ]]; then
    print -r -- "$script"
  else
    print -r -- "refresh.sh"
  fi
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__is_refresh_running() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local pid_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_pid_file "$root_dir")"
  if [[ ! -r "$pid_file" ]]; then
    return 1
  fi
  local pid
  pid="$(cat -- "$pid_file" 2>/dev/null)"
  [[ -n "$pid" ]] || return 1
  kill -0 "$pid" 2>/dev/null
}

# Updated to use listen_target (can be .sock or TCP addr)
__gradle_fzf_completion__start_refresh_background() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local listen_target="$2"
  local header_idle="$3"

  mkdir -p "$root_dir/.gradle-completion" 2>/dev/null

  if __gradle_fzf_completion__is_refresh_running "$root_dir"; then
    __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "refresh_skipped" "reason=already_running"
    return 0
  fi

  local refresh_script
  refresh_script="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_script)"
  __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "refresh_started" "script=$refresh_script"

  local cache_file tmp_file pid_file
  cache_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__cached_entries_file "$root_dir")"
  tmp_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_tmp_file "$root_dir")"
  pid_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_pid_file "$root_dir")"

  (
    local rc
    local out

    if ! out="$($refresh_script "$root_dir" 2> >(cat 1>&2))"; then
      rc=$?
      rm -f -- "$tmp_file" 2>/dev/null || true
      rm -f -- "$pid_file" 2>/dev/null || true
      __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "refresh_failed" "exit=$rc"
      if [[ -n "$listen_target" && -n "$header_idle" ]]; then
        __gradle_fzf_completion__fzf_post_action "$listen_target" "change-header($header_idle)"
      fi
      exit 0
    fi

    print -r -- "$out" >| "$tmp_file"
    mv -f -- "$tmp_file" "$cache_file" 2>/dev/null || cp -f -- "$tmp_file" "$cache_file"
    rm -f -- "$tmp_file" 2>/dev/null || true
    rm -f -- "$pid_file" 2>/dev/null || true
    if [[ -n "$listen_target" ]]; then
      __gradle_fzf_completion__fzf_post_action "$listen_target" "reload(cat -- \"$cache_file\")"
    fi
    if [[ -n "$listen_target" && -n "$header_idle" ]]; then
      __gradle_fzf_completion__fzf_post_action "$listen_target" "change-header($header_idle)"
    fi
    __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "refresh_finished" "exit=0"
    exit 0
  ) &!

  # Record background PID so the UI can report progress.
  print -r -- "$!" >| "$pid_file" 2>/dev/null || true
}
# Send an action string to a running fzf instance started with --listen.
# If listen_target ends with .sock: use Unix domain socket.
# Otherwise treat it as TCP address (e.g. 127.0.0.1:6266).
__gradle_fzf_completion__fzf_post_action() {
  local listen_target="$1"
  local action="$2"

  [[ -n "$listen_target" ]] || return 0

  if [[ "$listen_target" == *.sock ]]; then
    [[ -S "$listen_target" ]] || return 0
    command curl --silent --show-error --fail --unix-socket "$listen_target" http -d "$action" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
  else
    command curl --silent --show-error --fail "http://$listen_target" -d "$action" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
  fi
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__print_candidates() {
  # Prints current candidates from the cache file.
  local root_dir="$1"
  local cache_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__cached_entries_file "$root_dir")"
  if [[ -r "$cache_file" ]]; then
    cat -- "$cache_file"
  fi
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__header_idle() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  print -r -- "$root_dir  |  Cancel: Esc/Ctrl+c  |  Refresh: Ctrl+r"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__header_refreshing() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  print -r -- "$root_dir  |  Cancel: Esc/Ctrl+c  |  Refresh: Ctrl+r  |  Refreshing..."
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__on_refresh_key() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local listen_target="$2"
  local header_idle="$3"

  __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "refresh_requested" "via=ctrl-r"
  __gradle_fzf_completion__start_refresh_background "$root_dir" "$listen_target" "$header_idle"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__initialize_entries() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local cache_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__cached_entries_file "$root_dir")"

  mkdir -p "$root_dir/.gradle-completion" 2>/dev/null

  # Prefer an initialize.sh next to this completion script, otherwise rely on PATH.
  local init_script="$__gradle_fzf_completion__script_dir/initialize.sh"
  if [[ ! -x "$init_script" ]]; then
    init_script="initialize.sh"
  fi

  __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "initialize" "script=$init_script"

  # Run initializer and cache its output.
  local out
  if ! out="$("$init_script" "$root_dir" 2> >(cat 1>&2))"; then
    local rc=$?
    __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "initialize_failed" "exit=$rc"
    return $rc
  fi

  # Write output exactly as lines; trim any empty final line(s) is OK.
  print -r -- "$out" >| "$cache_file"
  return 0
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__load_entries() {
  local root_dir="$1"
  local cache_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__cached_entries_file "$root_dir")"

  if [[ -r "$cache_file" ]]; then
    __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "initial_content_loaded" "source=cache"
    cat -- "$cache_file"
    return 0
  fi

  if ! __gradle_fzf_completion__initialize_entries "$root_dir"; then
    return $?
  fi

  __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "initial_content_loaded" "source=initialize"
  cat -- "$cache_file"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__append_to_lbuffer() {
  local text="$1"
  if [[ -z "$text" ]]; then
    return 0
  fi

  # Add a separating space unless the buffer is empty or already ends with whitespace.
  if [[ -n "$LBUFFER" && "$LBUFFER" != *[[:space:]] ]]; then
    LBUFFER+=" "
  fi
  LBUFFER+="$text"
}

__gradle_fzf_completion__compute_filter_and_prefix() {
  # Prints three lines:
  # 1) mode: "append" or "replace"
  # 2) prefix: the part of LBUFFER to keep (may be empty)
  # 3) filter: the initial filter text (may be empty)

  local lb="$LBUFFER"

  # If the buffer ends with whitespace, we are in append mode.
  if [[ -z "$lb" || "$lb" == *[[:space:]] ]]; then
    print -r -- "append"
    print -r -- "$lb"
    print -r -- ""
    return 0
  fi

  # Determine how many shell words are in the buffer.
  local -a words
  words=(${(z)lb})

  # If there's only the command word (no arguments yet), do not treat it as a filter.
  if (( ${#words} <= 1 )); then
    print -r -- "append"
    print -r -- "$lb"
    print -r -- ""
    return 0
  fi

  # Otherwise, treat the last token as an initial filter and replace it on acceptance.
  local filter prefix
  filter="$words[-1]"

  # Keep everything before the last token as the prefix (this normally includes the separating whitespace).
  prefix="${lb%$filter}"

  # Safety: ensure the prefix ends with whitespace so that replacement does not glue tokens together.
  if [[ -n "$prefix" && "$prefix" != *[[:space:]] ]]; then
    prefix+=" "
  fi

  print -r -- "replace"
  print -r -- "$prefix"
  print -r -- "$filter"
}

# Main ZLE widget
__gradle_fzf_completion__widget() {
  # Only handle our cases; otherwise fall back to normal completion.
  if ! __gradle_fzf_completion__should_activate || ! __gradle_fzf_completion__is_gradle_root; then
    zle expand-or-complete
    return 0
  fi

  local root_dir="$PWD"

  local mode prefix filter
  {
    local -a parts
    parts=(${(@f)$(__gradle_fzf_completion__compute_filter_and_prefix)})
    mode="$parts[1]"
    prefix="$parts[2]"
    filter="$parts[3]"
  }

  # Load candidates
  local entries
  if ! entries="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__load_entries "$root_dir")"; then
    # Initializer failed; do not modify prompt.
    return $?
  fi

  # No entries -> do nothing
  if [[ -z "$entries" ]]; then
    return 0
  fi

  local header_idle header_refreshing
  header_idle="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__header_idle "$root_dir")"
  header_refreshing="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__header_refreshing "$root_dir")"

  local cache_file pid_file self_script
  cache_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__cached_entries_file "$root_dir")"
  pid_file="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__refresh_pid_file "$root_dir")"
  self_script="$__gradle_fzf_completion__script_path"

  local listen_target listen_arg cleanup_listen
  cleanup_listen=""

  if __gradle_fzf_completion__fzf_supports_unix_socket_listen; then
    local fzf_sock
    fzf_sock="$root_dir/.gradle-completion/fzf-${$}-${RANDOM}.sock"
    rm -f -- "$fzf_sock" 2>/dev/null || true
    listen_target="$fzf_sock"
    listen_arg="$fzf_sock"
    cleanup_listen="$fzf_sock"
  else
    local port
    port="$(__gradle_fzf_completion__pick_listen_port)"
    listen_target="127.0.0.1:$port"
    listen_arg="$listen_target"
  fi

  local initial_header
  if __gradle_fzf_completion__is_refresh_running "$root_dir"; then
    initial_header="$header_refreshing"
  else
    initial_header="$header_idle"
  fi

  # Ctrl+R starts an async refresh; header shows progress and list reloads.
  # Note: fzf executes bind commands via /bin/sh, so we must not reference shell functions directly.
  local bind_refresh
  bind_refresh="ctrl-r:execute-silent(zsh -lc 'source \"$self_script\"; __gradle_fzf_completion__on_refresh_key \"$root_dir\" \"$listen_target\" \"$header_idle\"')+change-header($header_refreshing)"

  # Run fzf; Escape / Ctrl+C should cancel and restore prompt.
  local out key selected

  if [[ -n "$filter" ]]; then
    out=$(cat -- "$cache_file" 2>/dev/null | fzf \
      --no-multi \
      --height=40% \
      --reverse \
      --prompt="Gradle> " \
      --header="$initial_header" \
      --listen="$listen_arg" \
      --query="$filter" \
      --expect=esc,ctrl-c \
      --bind=ctrl-c:abort \
      --bind="$bind_refresh")
  else
    out=$(cat -- "$cache_file" 2>/dev/null | fzf \
      --no-multi \
      --height=40% \
      --reverse \
      --prompt="Gradle> " \
      --header="$initial_header" \
      --listen="$listen_arg" \
      --expect=esc,ctrl-c \
      --bind=ctrl-c:abort \
      --bind="$bind_refresh")
  fi
  local rc=$?

  if [[ -n "$cleanup_listen" ]]; then
    rm -f -- "$cleanup_listen" 2>/dev/null || true
  fi

  # When using --expect, the first line is the pressed key (or empty), the second line is the selection.
  key="${out%%$'\n'*}"
  selected="${out#*$'\n'}"
  if [[ "$out" != *$'\n'* ]]; then
    # Single-line output: no key captured, treat it as the selection.
    key=""
    selected="$out"
  fi

  # Cancellation: distinguish ESC vs Ctrl+C when possible.
  if [[ "$key" == "esc" || "$key" == "ctrl-c" ]]; then
    __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "user_cancelled" "via=$key"
    zle redisplay
    return 0
  fi

  # Fallback cancellation paths (fzf aborts or errors).
  if (( rc == 130 )); then
    __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "user_cancelled" "via=ctrl-c"
    zle redisplay
    return 0
  fi

  if (( rc != 0 )) || [[ -z "$selected" ]]; then
    # Any non-zero or empty selection: do nothing.
    return 0
  fi

  if [[ "$mode" == "replace" ]]; then
    # Replace the last argument token (used as initial filter).
    # Ensure a space between the command/prefix and the selected token.
    local p="$prefix"
    if [[ -n "$p" && "$p" != *[[:space:]] ]]; then
      p+=" "
    fi
    LBUFFER="$p$selected"
  else
    __gradle_fzf_completion__append_to_lbuffer "$selected"
  fi
  __gradle_fzf_completion__log "$root_dir" "completion_accepted" "selection=$selected"
  zle redisplay
}

# Register widget and bind TAB.
zle -N __gradle_fzf_completion__widget
bindkey '^I' __gradle_fzf_completion__widget
